WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

13
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!

14
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind

15
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide

16
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals

17
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real

18
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

19
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

20
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through

21
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it

22
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

23
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for

24
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,

25
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?

26
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!

27
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

28
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:56.930
<b>Pearl</b>

29
00:01:54.680 --> 00:01:56.930
Whoa!

30
00:01:56.930 --> 00:01:58.770
They wanna fight, too!

31
00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:01.810
I'm getting fired up!

32
00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:04.600
Boss Man! It's a deal, right?

33
00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:08.780
If I drive them off, I'm done
with chores. That's okay, right?

34
00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:10.150
Couldn't ask for more.

35
00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:14.740
This place can't take
a year of your "chores."

36
00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:16.450
Alright!

37
00:02:16.450 --> 00:02:21.120
You seriously want to be
King of the Pirates, kid?

38
00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:26.420
As long as we take that ship,
the Grand Line is nothing to be scared of!

39
00:02:27.210 --> 00:02:31.840
We can pull right up to an enemy ship
for a more effective ambush!

40
00:02:32.840 --> 00:02:37.140
It's better than pretending to be
a Marine ship or raising the white flag.

41
00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:40.560
It would be a perfect sneak attack.

42
00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:42.850
It's true that no one would think...

43
00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:46.520
...pirates are on board
such a goofy-looking ship.

44
00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:51.400
B-But Don... Even if we reenter
the Grand Line with it,

45
00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:55.660
what if we come across someone
like Hawk Eye Mihawk again?

46
00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:03.660
You're still afraid of
someone like that? Huh?!

47
00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:05.040
N-No...

48
00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:09.000
You think an ordinary human
can slice up a huge ship like that?!

49
00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:13.970
He must have a devil fruit power.

50
00:03:13.970 --> 00:03:18.010
Although those with devil fruit powers
are just myths to your average person,

51
00:03:18.010 --> 00:03:21.430
the Grand Line is crawling with them.

52
00:03:21.890 --> 00:03:26.940
Mihawk must have used some
strange power to carve up our ship.

53
00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:33.360
Even that Straw Hat brat will be
just another pirate on that sea.

54
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:40.370
But Red Leg Zeff sailed
there for an entire year.

55
00:03:42.830 --> 00:03:47.710
He must have had ways
of dealing with those monsters.

56
00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:53.800
I'm certain those methods
are recorded in his logbook!

57
00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:57.300
Perhaps he also wrote
something about the One Piece.

58
00:03:57.630 --> 00:04:00.050
Don Krieg's still got it!

59
00:04:00.050 --> 00:04:05.270
With that ship and logbook, we can
go after the One Piece again!

60
00:04:05.270 --> 00:04:07.310
Got that, guys?!

61
00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:09.650
Let's go! We're taking the restaurant!

62
00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:11.230
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

63
00:04:12.150 --> 00:04:14.940
This ship belongs to us, the cooks!

64
00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:17.780
Go to the operating room
and open up the fins.

65
00:04:17.780 --> 00:04:21.120
What? Open up the fins?

66
00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:23.490
That'll give the enemy a foothold!

67
00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:24.950
I don't mind.

68
00:04:24.950 --> 00:04:28.500
People eat inside, so we've
gotta keep the battle out here.

69
00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:32.250
If a battle breaks out in there,
the old fart will complain.

70
00:04:32.250 --> 00:04:34.380
Did you say something,
you damn brat?

71
00:04:34.380 --> 00:04:37.130
Yeah, I said you like
to complain! Now, go.

72
00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:38.470
O-Okay...!

73
00:04:41.220 --> 00:04:44.600
They're coming, they're coming!
They're finally coming!

74
00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:46.220
Here I go!

75
00:04:46.220 --> 00:04:49.020
Gum-Gum Rocket!

76
00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:51.310
He's flying over here!

77
00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:52.650
And...

78
00:04:52.650 --> 00:04:54.940
Gum-Gum...

79
00:05:07.290 --> 00:05:09.540
Check out the cabin boy! Not bad!

80
00:05:09.540 --> 00:05:11.080
Wh-What the hell...

81
00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:12.460
...is that guy?!

82
00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:17.340
The Grand Line is crawling
with guys like that?

83
00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:18.510
Sanji!

84
00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:22.300
Watch closely how he fights.

85
00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:26.180
I can't believe you attacked
the same restaurant that fed you.

86
00:05:26.180 --> 00:05:29.560
I'm gonna kick your ungrateful ass!

87
00:05:31.850 --> 00:05:34.810
You're going to fight on the water
with hardly a foothold?

88
00:05:34.810 --> 00:05:39.820
At the very least, I know devil fruit users
can't swim. Isn't that right,

89
00:05:39.820 --> 00:05:40.990
anchor boy?!

90
00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:43.320
Yep! I stretch instead!

91
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:49.250
Sanji! The fins are
gonna open up now!

92
00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:04.760
A platform is rising...

93
00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.640
out of the sea!

94
00:06:18.980 --> 00:06:21.900
Oh man, that's awesome!

95
00:06:26.120 --> 00:06:29.620
Now we can fight to our
heart's content, you pirate scum!

96
00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:30.870
I see.

97
00:06:30.870 --> 00:06:34.250
You gave us a battlefield to keep
the restaurant undamaged.

98
00:06:34.830 --> 00:06:38.750
That works out for us too,
since that ship's gonna be ours.

99
00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:42.170
This deal just keeps getting better.

100
00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:46.050
As if we'd let you have this restaurant!

101
00:06:46.050 --> 00:06:48.430
That's right! Don't take us lightly!

102
00:06:48.430 --> 00:06:50.970
We're fighting cooks!

103
00:06:58.730 --> 00:07:02.860
Take to the seas, Mackerel Head I,
the Baratie's very own battleship!

104
00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:06.700
Unless you wanna sleep
with the fishes, move!

105
00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:11.740
What the hell is that?

106
00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:14.210
So cool! I want one!

107
00:07:14.210 --> 00:07:15.920
Paddle faster!

108
00:07:15.920 --> 00:07:16.710
I'm trying!

109
00:07:18.710 --> 00:07:20.540
Fire!

110
00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:27.090
I'm gonna fall in!

111
00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:29.850
Alright! Good job!

112
00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:33.520
Patty! Carne! Give 'em hell!

113
00:07:35.730 --> 00:07:37.190
They're pretty good!

114
00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:42.400
Never mind those minnows!
The big catch is up ahead!

115
00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:44.150
Roger!

116
00:07:44.150 --> 00:07:46.950
Krieg! Get ready!

117
00:07:47.360 --> 00:07:52.910
Marvel at the power of the Sea Restaurant
Baratie's oceangoing weapon!

118
00:08:02.670 --> 00:08:04.670
What? Did we bump into something?

119
00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:06.590
Huh? We're stuck!

120
00:08:07.130 --> 00:08:09.180
I am Don Krieg...

121
00:08:09.930 --> 00:08:12.470
the man who will
rule this world's oceans!

122
00:08:12.470 --> 00:08:14.430
I told you that's gonna be me!

123
00:08:14.430 --> 00:08:17.690
I don't have time for your games!

124
00:08:22.610 --> 00:08:24.690
That's some killer strength!

125
00:08:33.160 --> 00:08:35.540
It's coming this way!

126
00:08:35.540 --> 00:08:38.080
It'll destroy the restaurant!

127
00:08:55.560 --> 00:08:56.640
– Sanji!
– Sanji!

128
00:08:56.640 --> 00:08:58.270
With... just his foot?!

129
00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:12.570
S-Such strong legs!

130
00:09:12.570 --> 00:09:15.410
He kicked that weird boat away!

131
00:09:15.950 --> 00:09:17.750
That foot technique...

132
00:09:17.750 --> 00:09:19.040
He's pretty good!

133
00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:24.750
Sanji, you son of a bitch!

134
00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:26.340
You tryin' to crush your allies?!

135
00:09:26.960 --> 00:09:27.710
Yeah.

136
00:09:27.710 --> 00:09:30.630
Don't "yeah" us, you crazy stew!

137
00:09:30.630 --> 00:09:35.470
You just about lost your
strongest allies, spaghetti head!

138
00:09:35.930 --> 00:09:41.100
Is this really the best time
for you cooks to be cracking jokes?

139
00:09:42.190 --> 00:09:43.810
Let's get them!

140
00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:54.370
Even with a weapon,
a cook's just a cook.

141
00:09:54.370 --> 00:09:57.740
We seasoned fighters
are way out of your league.

142
00:09:57.740 --> 00:10:02.370
Now, behave yourselves and go find
a restaurant on solid ground.

143
00:10:02.370 --> 00:10:06.040
Hey, you guys! Why are you letting
them mop the floor with you?!

144
00:10:06.040 --> 00:10:08.250
Aren't you fighting cooks?!

145
00:10:09.130 --> 00:10:10.210
They're too strong!

146
00:10:10.590 --> 00:10:13.380
They're not like anyone
we've fought before!

147
00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:16.970
Don't go thinking we're
anything like your average pirates.

148
00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:21.230
We're the Krieg Pirates,
conquerors of the East Blue.

149
00:10:21.230 --> 00:10:27.190
By decree of the Krieg Pirates,
this ship is already ours!

150
00:10:27.190 --> 00:10:29.480
I've been a cook for over a decade.

151
00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:31.820
I've worked for 300 restaurants.

152
00:10:31.820 --> 00:10:34.910
I always got fired for starting fights,
and life was rough.

153
00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:38.910
After countless restaurants,
we finally came here...

154
00:10:40.200 --> 00:10:41.910
Anybody there?!

155
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:48.380
<b>Help
 Wanted</b>

156
00:10:41.910 --> 00:10:45.540
Is this the restaurant
run by Red Leg Zeff?!

157
00:10:45.540 --> 00:10:48.380
This "Damn Cooks Wanted"
poster better be true!

158
00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:54.090
Yeah, it's true.

159
00:10:56.590 --> 00:11:00.510
Be they master criminals
or escaped convicts,

160
00:11:00.510 --> 00:11:05.140
if they're starving and find
their way to this restaurant,

161
00:11:05.140 --> 00:11:07.650
we'll feed them until they're stuffed.

162
00:11:07.650 --> 00:11:11.650
Can you handle that?!

163
00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:13.030
– Y-Yes, Chef!
– Y-Yes, Chef!

164
00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:11.900
<b>Help
 Wanted</b>

165
00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:21.910
We can't serve this vile soup
to paying customers!

166
00:11:22.330 --> 00:11:23.950
What did you hit me for?!

167
00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:25.710
It's a mark of resolve!

168
00:11:25.710 --> 00:11:27.210
Shut up!

169
00:11:27.210 --> 00:11:30.880
Be it brawling or cooking,
we're allowed to do whatever we like.

170
00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:33.960
No other restaurant compares!

171
00:11:33.960 --> 00:11:35.170
So they say.

172
00:11:35.170 --> 00:11:37.180
Got that, Krieg?

173
00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:41.640
In the kitchen,
every day is a fierce battle.

174
00:11:41.640 --> 00:11:46.140
Compared to that, the pirates
we're facing today are nothing!

175
00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:47.600
He's exactly right!

176
00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:48.650
Fight!

177
00:11:48.650 --> 00:11:49.310
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

178
00:11:49.310 --> 00:11:51.770
Protect Chef Zeff!

179
00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:51.770
Protect the restaurant!

180
00:12:04.540 --> 00:12:05.750
Wh-Who the...?

181
00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:16.550
What are you guys doing?

182
00:12:17.840 --> 00:12:19.890
What's up with that weirdo?

183
00:12:19.930 --> 00:12:27.850
<b>Pearl "the Invincible"
Commander, Second Unit
Krieg Pirates</b>

184
00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:24.890
Unassailable: hence invincible!

185
00:12:24.890 --> 00:12:27.850
The invincible member of the Krieg Pirates,

186
00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.480
Pearl, at your service.

187
00:12:30.850 --> 00:12:32.190
Pearl!

188
00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:35.150
Patty! Carne! Are you all right?!

189
00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:42.120
They're not all right because they received
a Pearl Present, my killer punch.

190
00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:48.210
Oh, he's got a nice knife!
Well, it's mine now.

191
00:12:49.040 --> 00:12:54.000
Hey, let go. Give it to me!
Let it go, you damn loser!

192
00:13:06.520 --> 00:13:09.100
He sure can kick!

193
00:13:09.100 --> 00:13:11.440
A kitchen knife is a cook's soul.

194
00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:15.070
Keep your dirty hands
off it, amateurs.

195
00:13:15.690 --> 00:13:16.780
Sanji...

196
00:13:17.360 --> 00:13:19.400
Hold tight to this and stay down.

197
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:22.490
I'll clean up this trash.

198
00:13:22.820 --> 00:13:25.990
We won't be beaten by a mere cook!

199
00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:35.590
"A mere cook"?

200
00:13:35.590 --> 00:13:38.010
Then how about I fillet you bastards?!

201
00:13:39.970 --> 00:13:43.140
You're pretty arrogant to cast
them aside with just kicks.

202
00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:45.100
Is that some sort of policy?

203
00:13:45.430 --> 00:13:47.430
A cook's hands are his livelihood.

204
00:13:47.430 --> 00:13:50.520
I can't risk them in a fight.

205
00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:53.060
These legs will take you down as well.

206
00:13:53.060 --> 00:13:54.520
Take me down?

207
00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:55.940
Ridiculous.

208
00:13:55.940 --> 00:14:00.990
I'm an invincible man who's won all
sixty-one of my battles without a scratch.

209
00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:05.910
I've never shed blood in battle,

210
00:14:05.910 --> 00:14:08.120
not even a single drop.

211
00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:10.950
Winning unharmed
is proof of my power.

212
00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:16.000
I'm a shield man and a gentleman.

213
00:14:16.420 --> 00:14:17.960
Elegant, am I not?

214
00:14:18.460 --> 00:14:21.420
Did he make a joke?
It wasn't funny at all.

215
00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:23.180
Hey, Straw Hat brat!

216
00:14:23.180 --> 00:14:25.260
Pay attention or you'll get hurt!

217
00:14:31.810 --> 00:14:34.810
Even battleship cannons
can't hurt me.

218
00:14:34.810 --> 00:14:36.770
I come out of any attack unharmed!

219
00:14:39.980 --> 00:14:42.280
Man, that was a surprise.

220
00:14:42.280 --> 00:14:43.990
Good thing I didn't fall in the sea.

221
00:14:47.660 --> 00:14:48.530
What?

222
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.620
Well, shit.

223
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:52.870
Blood! Oh, no!

224
00:14:52.870 --> 00:14:54.580
Pearl, don't worry!

225
00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:56.330
It's just a nosebleed!

226
00:14:56.330 --> 00:14:58.590
It's not as if you were
wounded in battle!

227
00:14:58.590 --> 00:15:01.050
Please calm down, Pearl!

228
00:15:01.050 --> 00:15:02.050
What's going on?

229
00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:05.010
Th-Th-Th-Th-These guys are dangerous!

230
00:15:05.380 --> 00:15:08.010
What's his deal? He's acting weird.

231
00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:10.470
Is a nosebleed that big a deal?

232
00:15:13.600 --> 00:15:15.560
Stop it, Pearl!

233
00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:17.940
It's just a nosebleed!
Don't lose your cool!

234
00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:22.360
What the heck is he about to do?

235
00:15:22.690 --> 00:15:28.370
Danger! Danger! Danger!

236
00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:33.830
Oh, no! It's started!

237
00:15:33.830 --> 00:15:37.000
When Pearl loses his cool,
he actually ignites!

238
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:38.040
What was that?

239
00:15:38.880 --> 00:15:42.590
Fire Pearl...

240
00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:46.010
Blowout!

241
00:15:47.970 --> 00:15:50.850
Pearl! Please stop!

242
00:15:52.930 --> 00:15:56.690
Burn! Between this blaze
and my flaming shield,

243
00:15:56.690 --> 00:15:58.900
you have no idea how invincible I am!

244
00:16:00.810 --> 00:16:04.900
Moron! He'll burn down
the ship we're commandeering!

245
00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:07.740
Ow, ow, ow, ow...

246
00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:07.150
Dammit!

247
00:16:07.150 --> 00:16:11.240
Crap! There's no escape
from a sea of flames on open water!

248
00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:13.950
This isn't good!
The restaurant will catch fire!

249
00:16:14.450 --> 00:16:16.460
The restaurant will burn?

250
00:16:16.460 --> 00:16:17.750
Burn! Burn!

251
00:16:17.750 --> 00:16:18.870
You son of a bitch!

252
00:16:19.210 --> 00:16:21.840
You'll get flambéed, Sanji!

253
00:16:22.750 --> 00:16:24.340
I'm not gonna let you...

254
00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:27.170
burn this restaurant down!

255
00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:32.930
Wh-What a lunatic!

256
00:16:32.930 --> 00:16:34.680
Does he want to be a human torch?!

257
00:16:35.270 --> 00:16:38.190
Even feral beasts
steer clear of Fire Pearl!

258
00:16:40.270 --> 00:16:41.560
Dumbass!

259
00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:44.150
No cook worth their salt
is afraid of a little fire!

260
00:16:44.150 --> 00:16:46.530
D-Dammit!

261
00:16:46.530 --> 00:16:48.570
He's so refined!

262
00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:50.410
Here I come!

263
00:16:55.080 --> 00:16:56.290
That was a solid hit!

264
00:16:56.290 --> 00:16:58.870
He broke through
Pearl the Invincible's wall!

265
00:17:03.880 --> 00:17:05.380
What's with this cook?

266
00:17:05.380 --> 00:17:07.260
He's off his rocker...!

267
00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:10.050
Y-Y-You insufferable...

268
00:17:10.050 --> 00:17:12.300
Fire! I need more fire!

269
00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:14.760
I need to fuel more fire pearls!

270
00:17:16.720 --> 00:17:18.230
No, the restaurant...!

271
00:17:18.230 --> 00:17:21.730
If the fire reaches
the kitchen, it'll explode!

272
00:17:21.730 --> 00:17:23.770
Chef Zeff! Please get out of the way!

273
00:17:23.770 --> 00:17:25.770
Chef Zeff!

274
00:17:36.030 --> 00:17:39.000
M-My fire pearls!

275
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.500
That was child's play!

276
00:17:41.830 --> 00:17:44.460
The gust from his kick
put out the flame!

277
00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:46.710
Oh, wow! That guy's superhuman!

278
00:17:46.710 --> 00:17:49.420
So Red Leg Zeff is still kicking?!

279
00:17:49.800 --> 00:17:52.340
That was awesome, Boss Man!

280
00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:53.640
Now that it's come to this,

281
00:17:53.640 --> 00:17:58.470
I'll sink you all with the fins
before the restaurant catches fire!

282
00:18:01.730 --> 00:18:04.190
Sanji! Watch out!

283
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:07.190
Oh no! He's surrounded by the blaze!

284
00:18:11.450 --> 00:18:12.280
Ow, ow, ow...

285
00:18:12.280 --> 00:18:13.530
Cabin Boy!

286
00:18:13.780 --> 00:18:17.160
Gum-Gum Bazooka!

287
00:18:18.990 --> 00:18:21.290
He knocked that iron ball back!
Ow, ow, ow...

288
00:18:21.290 --> 00:18:23.960
Ow, ow, ow!

289
00:18:37.850 --> 00:18:40.850
Pearl is really down this time!

290
00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:42.810
– Pearl...!
– Pearl...!

291
00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:44.730
What the hell?

292
00:18:44.730 --> 00:18:46.270
That guy sure was a dummy.

293
00:18:46.770 --> 00:18:48.650
They're all worthless...

294
00:18:48.650 --> 00:18:51.280
In the end, I can
only rely on myself.

295
00:18:57.320 --> 00:19:00.160
The battle ends here.

296
00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:18.740
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

297
00:19:18.940 --> 00:19:25.760
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

298
00:19:26.010 --> 00:19:32.860
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

299
00:19:32.980 --> 00:19:40.120
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

300
00:19:42.820 --> 00:19:45.500
Look where I am

301
00:19:47.730 --> 00:19:53.910
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

302
00:19:54.250 --> 00:20:01.180
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

303
00:20:01.340 --> 00:20:08.260
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

304
00:20:08.390 --> 00:20:15.390
Take me to the place where memories remain

305
00:20:15.490 --> 00:20:21.260
Please don't ever let them fade
